Question: There are both gray and white section of  fur on a single wolf whose body is facing right with their head tilted left forward.

Reference Answer: True

Original program:

```
ANSWER0=VQA(image=LEFT,question='How many wolves are in the image?')
ANSWER1=VQA(image=RIGHT,question='How many wolves are in the image?')
ANSWER2=VQA(image=LEFT,question='Is the wolf's body facing right?')
ANSWER3=VQA(image=RIGHT,question='Is the wolf's body facing right?')
ANSWER4=VQA(image=LEFT,question='Is the wolf's head tilted left forward?')
ANSWER5=VQA(image=RIGHT,question='Is the wolf's head tilted left forward?')
ANSWER6=VQA(image=LEFT,question='Are there both gray and white sections of fur on the wolf?')
ANSWER7=VQA(image=RIGHT,question='Are there both gray and white sections of fur on the wolf?')
ANSWER8=EVAL(expr='{ANSWER0} == 1 and {ANSWER2} and {ANSWER4} and {ANSWER6}')
ANSWER9=EVAL(expr='{ANSWER1} == 1 and {ANSWER3} and {ANSWER5} and {ANSWER7}')
ANSWER10=EVAL(expr='{ANSWER8} xor {ANSWER9}')
FINAL_ANSWER=RESULT(var=ANSWER10)
```
